Following price gains recorded by most high value stocks, trading on the equities sector of the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE), closed upbeat yesterday, as the All-Share Index appreciated 0.66 per cent.
   
Specifically, at the close of transactions, Tuesday, the All Share Index (ASI), increased by 150.38 absolute points, representing a gain of 0.66 per cent to close at 22,780.30 points. Similarly, the market capitalisation rose by N78billion to close at N11.872trillion.
   
The uptrend was impacted by gains recorded in large and medium capitalised stocks, amongst which were; Lafarge Africa, Zenith Bank, BUA Cement, Guaranty Trust Bank and PZ Cussons Nigeria.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .